cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.NE 

This paper deals with object detection using deep convolutional neural networks, specifically for detecting weeds in farm land. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of ResNet, a popular deep learning architecture, which falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses the use of data augmentation and dropout techniques, which are commonly used in deep learning, and therefore could also fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses the use of region-based fully convolutional networks (R-FCN), which is a technique used for object detection, and therefore could fall under cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the paper discusses the use of deep residual networks (ResNets), which are a type of neural network, and therefore could also fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
